    <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
    <p>
      Cookies are small text files that are stored on your device (computer, smartphone, or tablet) when you visit a website. They help websites remember your preferences, improve your experience, and provide analytics to website operators.
    </p>
    <p>
      Cookies can be either "session cookies" (deleted when you close your browser) or "persistent cookies" (remain on your device for a set period or until you delete them manually).
    </p>
  </section>

